From 9e8df1d945abb914ea29a8d931bd9c3987171d81 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Yakov Till <yakov.till@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 14 Dec 2025 13:46:32 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 16/17] ALSA: hda: aw88399: implement complete startup sequence
 in library

The library's aw88399_dev_start_internal() was incomplete compared to
the vendor driver in aw88399.c. This caused robustness issues and
'pa stop check fail' errors in dmesg.

Changes:
- Fix I2S TX enable to use correct register (I2SCTRL3_REG, not I2SCFG1)
- Add PLL lock check with mode1/mode2 fallback (aw_dev_check_syspll)
- Add full system status check with noise gate awareness (aw_dev_check_sysst)
- Add DSP watchdog status check (aw_dev_dsp_check)
- Add interrupt status clear function (aw_dev_clear_int_status)
- Rewrite start sequence to match vendor driver:
  1. Power on
  2. PLL lock check
  3. Amp power on
  4. System status check
  5. DSP check (if enabled)
  6. I2S TX enable
  7. Unmute
  8. Clear interrupts
- Add proper error handling with cleanup on failure

The startup sequence now matches the original aw88399_dev_start() from
the vendor's ASoC driver, providing the same robustness and error
recovery behavior.

Signed-off-by: Yakov Till <yakov.till@gmail.com>
